About Me

I'm Victoria Omoshade — an Operations & Automation Specialist who turns fragmented workflows into clean, scalable systems. My work spans Zapier automations, CRM pipelines, support ops, data management, and web builds.

I believe every business problem has a systems solution. Whether it's a SaaS startup losing leads between tools, or a restaurant without documented processes — I diagnose, design, and deliver the fix.

This portfolio mirrors my Google Drive structure exactly: organized by folder and subfolder, with every project documented through its own case study, screenshots, and deliverable files.

Operational Reports

🍽️
📁 Reports / Operational Diagnosis Report
Spice Haven Restaurant — Operations Diagnosis

A full operational audit for a single-outlet restaurant operating for 3 years. Despite high food ratings, the business was struggling with consistency and efficiency. I diagnosed the root causes and delivered a structured report with actionable recommendations.

Challenge
Order delays, wrong items served, inconsistent complaint handling, staff role confusion, and frequent stock shortages
Root Cause
No documented SOPs · Undefined roles · Verbal-only communication · No complaint process
Business Impact
Lost repeat customers · Revenue leakage from wastage & refunds · Zero owner visibility into daily performance
Recommendation
Document all operating procedures · Clarify role definitions · Build a structured complaint resolution workflow
Conclusion
The challenges facing Spice Haven are operational, not product-based. Documenting procedures and clarifying roles will reduce costs, improve satisfaction, and build a sustainable business.
